revision.text:
{{Expand language|topic=|langcode=ja|otherarticle=都久夫須麻神社|date=December 2021}}
{{Infobox religious building | name = Tsukubusuma Shrine | image = Chikubusumajinja02s3200.jpg | caption = Main shrine of Tsukubusuma Shrine, designated as a [[National Treasure (Japan)|National Treasure]]. | map_type = Japan | map_alt = | coordinates = {{coord|35.4207|136.1442|type:landmark_region:JP|format=dms|display=title,inline}} | map_relief = | map_size = | map_caption = | religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]] | type = | deity = | founded_by = | established = | date_destroyed = | location = | website = | architecture_style = | festival = | leadership = }} '''Tsukubusuma Shrine''' (都久夫須麻神社, ''Tsukubusuma Jinja'') is a [[Shinto]] shrine on [[Chikubu Island]] in [[Shiga Prefecture]], Japan. Its {{nihongo|main hall|本殿|honden}} is a [[National Treasure (Japan)|National Treasure of Japan]]. The shrine's main festival is held annually on June 15. It is also called '''Chikubushima Shrine''' (竹生島神社, ''Chikubushima Jinja'').
==See also== * [[List of National Treasures of Japan (shrines)]]
==References== *Joseph Cali with John Dougill, ''Shinto Shrines: A Guide to the Sacred Sites of Japan's Ancient Religion'' (University of Hawai'i Press, 2013).
